	"contentText": "Week 10\n  \n  \n  \n    \n\n\n\nOverview\n\n\n\n\nDiversifiable or unsystematic risk, unidversifable or systematic risk, achieving diversification through portfolios, index models, calculating the alpha and beta of an asset, Treynor-Black Model\n \n\n\n\n\nLearning Objectives\nUpon completion of this week, you will be able to understand:\n\nhow diversification helps reduce risk in a portfolio\ndecompose the risk of an asset into systematic and idiosyncratic components\nlink between systematic risk and exposure to macroeconomic variables\nthe market as the source of systematic risk in single index models\ncalculate the alpha and the beta of an asset\nuse single index models to simplify the portfolio allocation problem\nwith single index models the optimal risky portfolio becomes a combination of an active portfolio and a passive portfolio (the Treynor-Black model)\n\n \nPreparation for class\nMandatory reading: lecture 5.pdf\n    \n\nDownload lecture 5.pdf\nData: index models data.xls\n    \n\nDownload index models data.xls\nData: TreynorBlack Data.xlsx\n    \n\nDownload TreynorBlack Data.xlsx\nSupplement: lecture 5 supplement.pdf\n    \n\nDownload lecture 5 supplement.pdf\n\n\n\n\n \nMidterm exam preparation\nStudy guide: midterm study guide.pdf\n    \n\nDownload midterm study guide.pdf\nPractice Midterm: Practice Midterm\nPractice Midterm data: data_pm.xlsx\n    \n\nDownload data_pm.xlsx\n \nMidterm exam\nMidterm exam: Midterm Exam\nMidterm exam work upload: Midterm Exam Work Upload\n \n \nClass\nClass zoom link: Class logistics\n \n \nClass Notes\nOct 23 class recording: \nhttps://cuboulder.zoom.us/rec/share/NsjalS9ebhLPt2HlgwAd5X-sa_JKB2odpmZcIfVYwCkDOiyu6yiUHwMDbyTaxDzr.bt7U0bmD19-pJzi6\n    \n\nLinks to an external site.\nPasscode: g=AQL9cP\n \n  \n  \n\n",
